10 things i learned in 2022:☆

1. putting yourself first is not selfish. 
2. controlling the way you react toward anything (good or bad) is a super power.
3. cutting negative energy out of your life is a form of self care. 
4. it’s healthy to take days off.
5. the only opinion that matters is your own. 
6. trust is earned not given. 
7. the “perfect” moment doesn’t exist…execute NOW.
8. aging is beautiful. 
9. being alone is when i thrive the most.
10. not everyone is going to give you the same respect you give them, and that’s ok. 

HAPPY 2023 EVERYONE!! I can’t wait to see what this year teaches me💅🏻

6 skin tips i used this week that actually work: 
1. ICE (morning and night trust me) 
2. at home facial lymphatic drainage…every morning (i use grape seed oil) 
3. any crème face masks + eye patches (my favorite one is “be juicy”🦊
3. high frequency wand (kills bacteria under the skin-but pls be careful and learn about it before you use it) 
4. self tanner as makeup before bed (i did lip liner, contour, + eyeshadow-saves time getting ready in the AM)
5. sea moss first thing in the morning + right before bed 
6. mighty patch pimple stickers (the invisible ones)

**bonus that i’ve been i’ve been preaching for YEARS-organic castor oil on brows + lashes every night before bed**
